{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-08",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_08_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "08 - The Queen's Croquet-ground",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.605,
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 729.76,
  "page_end_sec": 821.3,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 729.76,
      "end": 731.22,
      "text": "When she got back to the Cheshire Cat,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 731.42,
      "end": 733.56,
      "text": "she was surprised to find quite a large crowd"
    },
    {
      "start": 733.74,
      "end": 734.54,
      "text": "collected round it:"
    },
    {
      "start": 735.06,
      "end": 737.62,
      "text": "there was a dispute going on between the executioner,"
    },
    {
      "start": 737.74,
      "end": 738.24,
      "text": "the King,"
    },
    {
      "start": 738.42,
      "end": 739.04,
      "text": "and the Queen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 739.42,
      "end": 740.66,
      "text": "who were all talking at once,"
    },
    {
      "start": 740.76,
      "end": 742.52,
      "text": "while all the rest were quite silent,"
    },
    {
      "start": 742.64,
      "end": 743.72,
      "text": "and looked very uncomfortable."
    },
    {
      "start": 745.1,
      "end": 746.16,
      "text": "The moment Alice appeared,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 746.42,
      "end": 748.94,
      "text": "she was appealed to by all three to settle the question,"
    },
    {
      "start": 749.1,
      "end": 751.02,
      "text": "and they repeated their arguments to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.18,
      "end": 753.28,
      "text": "though, as they all spoke at once,"
    },
    {
      "start": 753.38,
      "end": 756.58,
      "text": "she found it very hard indeed to make out exactly what they said."
    },
    {
      "start": 758.08,
      "end": 760.8,
      "text": "The executioner's argument was, that you couldn't",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 760.8,
      "end": 763.2,
      "text": "cut off a head unless there was a body to cut it"
    },
    {
      "start": 763.2,
      "end": 763.62,
      "text": "off from:"
    },
    {
      "start": 763.8,
      "end": 766.12,
      "text": "that he had never had to do such a thing before,"
    },
    {
      "start": 766.34,
      "end": 768.0,
      "text": "and he wasn't going to begin at"
    },
    {
      "start": 768.14,
      "end": 769.02,
      "text": "_his_ time of life."
    },
    {
      "start": 769.86,
      "end": 771.72,
      "text": "The King's argument was, that anything",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 771.72,
      "end": 773.66,
      "text": "that had a head could be beheaded,"
    },
    {
      "start": 774.02,
      "end": 775.66,
      "text": "and that you weren't to talk nonsense."
    },
    {
      "start": 776.68,
      "end": 779.58,
      "text": "The Queen's argument was, that if something wasn't done about",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 779.58,
      "end": 781.06,
      "text": "it in less than no time,"
    },
    {
      "start": 781.16,
      "end": 783.36,
      "text": "she'd have everybody executed all round."
    },
    {
      "start": 784.08,
      "end": 785.52,
      "text": "(It was this last remark that"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.52,
      "end": 787.76,
      "text": "had made the whole party look so grave and anxious.)"
    },
    {
      "start": 788.768,
      "end": 790.44,
      "text": "Alice could think of nothing else to say,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 790.76,
      "end": 792.5,
      "text": "but \"It belongs to the Duchess:"
    },
    {
      "start": 792.54,
      "end": 793.94,
      "text": "you'd better ask _her_ about it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 795.712,
      "end": 798.2,
      "text": "\"She's in prison,\" the Queen said to the executioner;",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 798.688,
      "end": 799.22,
      "text": "\"fetch her here.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 800.08,
      "end": 802.26,
      "text": "And the executioner went off like an arrow."
    },
    {
      "start": 802.88,
      "end": 805.9,
      "text": "The Cat's head began fading away the moment he was gone,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 806.24,
      "end": 808.68,
      "text": "and by the time he had come back with the Duchess,"
    },
    {
      "start": 808.72,
      "end": 810.22,
      "text": "it had entirely disappeared;"
    },
    {
      "start": 810.84,
      "end": 812.62,
      "text": "so the King and the executioner ran"
    },
    {
      "start": 812.62,
      "end": 814.48,
      "text": "wildly up and down looking for it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 814.86,
      "end": 816.88,
      "text": "while the rest of the party went back to the game."
    },
    {
      "start": 820.38,
      "end": 821.3,
      "text": "End of chapter 8",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}